.TH pulsar-daemon 1 "Apache Pulsar" "Version 4.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pulsar-daemon \- Pulsar daemon management utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pulsar-daemon
(start|stop|restart) <command> [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
pulsar-daemon is a utility for starting, stopping, and restarting Pulsar
components as background daemons. It manages process lifecycle and logging.

Note: In production environments, it is recommended to use systemd service
files instead of pulsar-daemon for better process management.

.SH COMMANDS
The following components can be managed:
.TP
.B broker
Run a broker server
.TP
.B bookie
Run a bookie server
.TP
.B proxy
Run a Proxy Pulsar service
.TP
.B websocket
Run a websocket proxy server
.TP
.B functions-worker
Run a functions worker server
.TP
.B autorecovery
Run an autorecovery service
.TP
.B standalone
Run a standalone Pulsar service (development only)
.TP
.B zookeeper
Run a zookeeper server
.TP
.B configuration-store
Run a configuration-store server

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -force
(Only with stop command) Forcefully stop the server if normal shutdown fails

.SH EXAMPLES
Start broker as daemon:
.RS
pulsar-daemon start broker
.RE

Stop broker daemon:
.RS
pulsar-daemon stop broker
.RE

Force stop bookie:
.RS
pulsar-daemon stop bookie -force
.RE

.SH FILES
.TP
/etc/apache-pulsar/
Configuration files
.TP
/usr/lib/apache-pulsar/
Pulsar installation directory
.TP
/var/log/apache-pulsar/
Log files directory

.SH SEE ALSO
pulsar(1), systemctl(1)

